.TH MASTODON\-MCP 1 "2026-04-30" "mastodon-mcp-server 1.0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mastodon\-mcp \- Model Context Protocol server for Mastodon integration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mastodon\-mcp
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
[\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mastodon\-mcp
is a Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that provides AI assistants and
other MCP-compatible clients with access to Mastodon social network
functionality via the Mastodon.py library.
.PP
The server communicates over standard input/output (stdio) by default, or
optionally over HTTP using the streamable-HTTP transport.  It is configured
entirely through environment variables; no configuration files are required.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version number and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MASTODON_INSTANCE
URL of the Mastodon instance to connect to (required).
Example: \fIhttps://mastodon.social\fR
.TP
.B MASTODON_ACCESS_TOKEN
OAuth 2.0 access token for authentication (required).
.TP
.B MASTODON_MCP_TRANSPORT
Transport mode.  Accepted values: \fBstdio\fR (default) or
\fBstreamable\-http\fR.
.TP
.B MASTODON_MCP_HOST
Bind address for the HTTP transport (default: \fI127.0.0.1\fR).
.TP
.B MASTODON_MCP_PORT
TCP port for the HTTP transport (default: \fI8000\fR).
.TP
.B MASTODON_MCP_STATELESS_HTTP
Set to \fBtrue\fR, \fB1\fR, or \fByes\fR to disable HTTP session state
(default: \fIfalse\fR).
.TP
.B READ_ONLY
Set to \fBtrue\fR, \fB1\fR, or \fByes\fR to restrict the server to
read-only Mastodon operations (default: \fIfalse\fR).
.TP
.B DEBUG
Set to any non-empty value to enable verbose logging (default: disabled).
.SH EXAMPLES
Run as a stdio MCP server (typical usage with an AI client):
.PP
.RS
.nf
MASTODON_INSTANCE=https://mastodon.social \\
MASTODON_ACCESS_TOKEN=<token> \\
mastodon\-mcp
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run as an HTTP MCP server on port 8080:
.PP
.RS
.nf
MASTODON_MCP_TRANSPORT=streamable\-http \\
MASTODON_MCP_PORT=8080 \\
MASTODON_INSTANCE=https://mastodon.social \\
MASTODON_ACCESS_TOKEN=<token> \\
mastodon\-mcp
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/mastodon\-mcp\-server/.env
Optional dotenv file loaded at startup (not installed by default).
